<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="92" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1462,1991]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1462,1487]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992" authorityName="Okada &amp; Sidorenko" authorityYear="1992" box="[573,1043,1462,1487]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toyaensis">
<emphasis box="[573,712,1463,1486]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">S. toyaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Okada, T. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S." box="[727,1043,1462,1487]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" pagination="655 - 662" refId="ref10701" refString="Okada, T. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S. (1992) New or unrecorded species of Stegana (Steganina) (Diptera, Drosophilidae) from the Old World, especially Japan and Russia. Japanese Journal of Entomology, 60, 655 - 662." type="journal article" year="1992">
Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 
<quantity box="[987,1043,1463,1487]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05968" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" unit="in" value="1992.0">1992</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in some characters of the male terminalia, but can be distinguished by the mesonotum dark brown, with 1 thin, unconspicuous, yellow longitudinal stripe medially, yellowish brown laterally (
<figureCitation box="[793,885,1534,1559]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; B–J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); aedeagus slightly flat apically in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,286,1570,1595]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1577,1599]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,447,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1435,411,1573]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 6. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624698/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Fig. 6C, D</figureCitation>
). The minimum interspecific genetic distance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Okada &amp; Sidorenko" authorityYear="1992" box="[848,982,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toyaensis">
<emphasis box="[848,982,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">S. toyaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 3.5%, which is smaller than to other species (
<tableCitation box="[246,334,1606,1631]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="23.[147,225,546,566]" captionText="TABLE 2. Genetic distances within and between the 130 mtCOI sequences of 38 species of the coleoptrata, ornatipes, and undulata groups involved in the molecular analysis." pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="93" pageId="11" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1462,1991]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1642,1667]" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Description.</emphasis>
Male: Frons black. First flagellomere yellow on basal 2/3, black on distal 1/3. Clypeus and palpus yellow. Katepisternum entirely white. Scutellum black (
<figureCitation box="[866,957,1678,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; B–J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Femur of foreleg with 4 long erect setae near distal part of posteroventral surface. Abdominal tergites dark brown to black (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1176,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[255,1340,253,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[251,1340,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus. A. Stegana (Steganina) toyaensis Okada &amp; Sidorenko, 1992; B–J in holotype: B. Stegana (Steganina) latitabula sp. nov.; C. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov.; D. Stegana (Steganina) pinguifoliacea sp. nov.; E. Stegana (Steganina) spatulata, sp. nov.; F. Stegana (Steganina) stachydifolia, sp. nov.; G. Stegana (Steganina) hirtifoliacea sp. nov.; H. Stegana (Steganina) unguiculata sp. nov.; I. Stegana (Steganina) biflava sp. nov.; J. Stegana (Steganina) flavivittata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624690/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1577,1599]" captionTargetBox="[181,1397,447,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1435,411,1573]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 6. Stegana (Steganina) panda sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (inner view); C, D. Hypandrium, parameres, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views); E, F. Gonopods (ventral and lateral views); G. Tenth sternite (ventral view). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2624698/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="92">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
): Epandrium slightly protruded ventrally, with numerous setae on posterior portion per side. Surstylus with numerous setulae basally. Cercus lacking pubescence. Tenth sternite broadened, with 1 pair of processes submedially. Paramere with 1 setula.
</paragraph>
